com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.server.rest

Class RestRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.server.rest.RestRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Stringable, Comparable<RestRequest>

    @Immutable
public final class RestRequest
extends Object
implements Stringable, Comparable<RestRequest>
    Represents a REST request. Such request has two informational parts: method and URI.

      • valueOf

        public static final RestRequest valueOf(String method,
                                        String uri)
                                 throws RestRequestSyntaxException
        Returns RestRequest that corresponds to the provided method and uri.
        Parameters:
        method - A String that represents RestMethod.
        uri - A String that represents URI part of a RestRequest. Value of this parameter MUST obey rules specified in the URI.URI(String) constructor. The leading character MUST be solidus ('/', U+002F).

        All parts of uri that aren't related to URI.getPath() are ignored, but can be accessed via the getUri() method.

        Returns:
        RestRequest that corresponds to the provided method and uri.
        Throws:
        RestRequestSyntaxException - If arguments violate RestRequest syntax.

      • getUriNodes

        public final List<String> getUriNodes()
        Returns nodes of a URI of the RestRequest. Each node MAY contain any characters except solidus ('/', U+002F) character. Nodes are calculated from a URI by splitting (from left to right) path of the URI.

        Examples:

        • request with URI "/some/element/by%20this_id/" contains 3 nodes "some", "element" and "by this_id"
        • request with URI "/" contains 1 node ""
        Returns:
        Unmodifiable List of nodes of the RestRequest that contains at least one element.
        See Also:
        getUri()
